yoruba_text: Wolfgang, tí ó ti di alà gbà bá yìí, rá ntí ìbẹ̀wò ọlọ́rẹ̀ẹ́-sọ́rẹ̀ẹ́ tí ìrá nṣẹ́ iṣẹ́ òjíṣẹ́ kan à ti ìyà wó rẹ̀ ṣe sọ́dọ̀ ìdílé rẹ̀.
english_text: Wolfgang, now an elder, recalls a social visit made on his family by a ministerial servant and his wife.

yoruba_text: Wolfgang, tó jẹ́ agbẹjọ́rò ṣà làyé pé: “Ohun tó dáa gan-an ni lá ti gbẹ́kẹ̀ lé ẹnì kan tó fẹ́ ire ẹni, ìyẹn ẹni tó lè ṣe ohun tó dá ra jù lọ fún ọ, tó sì máa ṣe é ní ti gidi!”
english_text: Wolfgang, a legal adviser, explains: “It's wonderful to be able to lean on someone who has your best interests at heart, someone who can —and actually will— do what's best for you!”

yoruba_text: Wolfgangà ti aya rẹ̀ pà dé ọkùnrin náà ní ọjọ́ mẹ́ta lẹ́yìn náà.
english_text: Wolfgangand his wife met the man three days later.

yoruba_text: A lá yọ̀ pé ọmọkùnrin waWolfgangà ti aya rẹ̀ wà lẹ́nu iṣẹ́ alá bòójútó à yíká à ti pé ọmọkùnrin tiwọn náà ń sìn gẹ́gẹ́ bí alá bòójútó à yíká pẹ̀lú.
english_text: We are happy that our son Wolfgangand his wife are in the circuit work and that their son also serves as a circuit overseer.

yoruba_text: Akéwì ọmọ ilẹ̀ Já mánì kan tó ń jẹ́ JohannWolfgangvon Goethe sọ pé: “Ní tèmi, mo fẹ́ràn Bíbélì mo sì bọ̀wọ̀ fún un gan-an, to rí òun ló jẹ́ kí n mọ èyí tó pọ̀ jù nínú ìwà dá ad áa tí mò ń hù.”
english_text: German poet Johann Wolfgangvon Goethe wrote: “For my part, I loved and revered [the Bible], because I owed almost my whole development in moral culture to it.”

yoruba_text: Ọkùnrin kan tó ń jẹ́Wolfgangtó ti gbéyà wó sílé lá ti ọdún má rùndínlógójì sọ pé: “Témi à tìyà wó mí bá ń sọ̀rọ̀ nípa à wọn ìṣòro kan tó wà ń lẹ̀, ọkàn mi máa ń dà rú, pà ápàá tí mo bá rí i pé ìyà wó mi ò lóye èrò tèmi.”
english_text: Wolfgang, who has been married for 35 years, says, “When we discuss problems, I get kind of tense inside, especially when I feel that my wife doesn't understand my way of thinking.”

yoruba_text: Kódà gan-an, wọn kò gbà kíWolfgangọmọ mi tó jẹ́ ọmọ ọdún mẹ́rin máa sọ̀rọ̀ nípa “Dá dì” à fi kí ó sọ̀rọ̀ nípa “Ome Jan” (Ará kùnrin Jòhá nù).
english_text: Even my four-year-old son, Wolfgang, was not allowed to speak about “Dad” but only about “Ome Jan” (Uncle John).

yoruba_text: BíWolfgangRosenthal tó léwá jú nínú ìwá dìí Süddeutsche Zeitung náà ṣe sọ: “A ti fìdí rẹ̀ múlẹ̀ pé ìgbì omi tó ń ṣà dédé ru gùdù wọ́pọ̀ dá ad áa ju bí ẹni kẹ́ni ṣe lè rò lọ.”
english_text: According to the Süddeutsche Zeitung, project leader Wolfgang Rosenthal says: “We have proved that monster waves are more common than anyone thought.”

english_text: Wolfgang Capito was a young man with deep religious convictions.

yoruba_text: Wolfgangsọ pé: “Àtìgbà tá a ti túbọ̀ ń lépa nǹkan tẹ̀mí ni inú wa ti ń dùn ju ti tẹ́lẹ̀ lọ, ọkàn wa sì ti balẹ̀ sí i.
english_text: Wolfgangsays: “Ever since we became more involved in pursuing spiritual things, we have been happier and have experienced more satisfaction.

yoruba_text: Bá wo ni fífi Kọ́ríń tì Kíní 15:33 sílò ṣe lè ràn wá lọ́wọ́ lá ti lépa ìwà funfun?
english_text: How can the application of 1 Corinthians 15:33 help us to pursue virtue today?

yoruba_text: (Sá àmù 25:4) Dídá kẹ́kọ̀ọ́ Bíbélì à ti à wọn ìwé Society lè ràn ọ́ lọ́wọ́ lá ti túbọ̀ mọ Jèhófà sí i.
english_text: (Psalm 25:4) Personal study of the Bible and of the Society's publications can help you become better acquainted with Jehovah.

yoruba_text: Ṣé wọ́n máa ń sọ òtítọ́?
english_text: Dotheyspeak the truth?

yoruba_text: Kò ṣòro rá rá fún à wọn Kristian tí wọ́n ní ojúlówó ọkàn-ìfẹ́ nínú araawọn lá ti fi ìfẹ́ wọn hàn nígbà ki gbà nínú ọdún.
english_text: Christians who have a genuine interest in one another find no difficulty in spontaneously expressing theirloveat any time of the year.

yoruba_text: (7) Wọ́n ń fi bí a ṣe lè ká pá à wọn ìṣòro òde òní hàn.
english_text: (7)Theyshow how to cope with today's problems.

yoruba_text: Níbẹ̀, wọ́n á kọ́ lá ti máa lo Bíbélì à tà wọn ìwé tó dá lórí Bíbélì, wọ́n á sì máa fi ojú tó tọ́ wò wọ́n.
english_text: There, theylearn to use and respect the Bible and Bible-based literature.

yoruba_text: (1 Sá múẹ́lì 25:41; 2 Àwọn Ọba 3:11) Ẹ̀yin òbí, ǹjẹ́ ẹ máa ń gba à wọn ọmọ yín kékeré à tà wọn tó wà lọ́dọ̀ọ́ níyà njú pé kí wọ́n máa fayọ̀ ṣe iṣẹ́ èyí kéyìí tá a bá fún wọn ṣe, ì báà jẹ́ ní Gbọ̀ngàn Ìjọba tà bí ní gbọ̀ngàn à péjọ?
english_text: (1 Samuel 25:41; 2 Kings 3:11) Parents, do you encourage your children and teenagers to work cheerfully at any assignment thattheyare given to do, whether at the Kingdom Hall, at an assembly, or at a convention site?

yoruba_text: Bí wọ́n bá ń pinnu ohun tí wọ́n máa ṣe, wọn kò gbọ́dọ̀ gbà gbé lá ti ronú lórí ohun tí Jèhófà máa fẹ́ kí wọ́n ṣe.
english_text: In making their decision, theymust not fail to consider how Jehovah feels about whattheyare doing.

yoruba_text: 24 Lẹ́yìn náà, à wọn kan lá ra à wọn tó wà pẹ̀lú wa lọ sí ibojì* náà,+ wọ́n sì bá ibẹ̀ bí à wọn obìnrin náà ṣe sọ gẹ́lẹ́, à mọ́ wọn ò rí i.”
english_text: 24 Then some of those who were with us went off to the tomb,*+ andtheyfound it just as the women had said, buttheydid not see him.”

yoruba_text: Àsọtẹ́lẹ̀ nípa ìparun Jerúsá lẹ́mù jẹ́ ká rí i kedere pé Jèhófà jẹ́ Ọlọ́run tó máa ń 'jẹ́ kí à wọn èèyàn rẹ̀ mọ̀ nípa à wọn ohun tuntun kí wọ́n tó ṣẹlẹ̀.'—Aísá yà 42:9.
english_text: The prophecy regarding the destruction of Jerusalem clearly portrays Jehovah as a God who 'causes his people to know new things beforetheybegin to spring up.' —Isaiah 42:9.

yoruba_text: ọ̀wọ́n
english_text: beloved · dear · precious
